channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: Homa cookin’ for second PGA win in California
item.description: Max Homa roared to the finish Sunday with an eagle and three birdies on the back nine to fire a 65 and capture the PGA Tour's season-opening Fortinet Championship in Napa, California.

item.title: Most ridiculous triple-0 calls revealed
item.description: Australians are being kept in life-and-death situations for far longer than necessary because others are calling triple-0 asking for directions and recipes.

item.title: Biden asks for early Macron talks as allies try to smooth tensions
item.description: The United States and Britain sought Sunday to smooth tensions with Paris over a new security pact with Australia, with US President Joe Biden requesting early talks with his French counterpart Emmanuel Macron.

item.title: Violence erupts at construction protest
item.description: A violent brawl has erupted outside CFMEU headquarters after hundreds of people showed up to protest mandatory vaccinations for construction workers.

item.title: Netflix eyes top Emmy for ‘The Crown’ as ‘Ted Lasso’ scores wins
item.description: Television's top stars gathered for the first time in two years on Sunday at the Emmy Awards, where "The Crown" took four awards in the first hour and is tipped to finally win the small screen's biggest prize for Netflix.

item.title: Mexico’s suit against US gunmakers edges ahead
item.description: The US federal court examining Mexico's lawsuit against top US arms manufacturers has set deadlines for the case's first proceedings, foreign ministry officials said Sunday.

item.title: Woman attacked on morning walk: cops
item.description: A 20-year-old man is in police custody after the wounding of a 34-year-old woman on the Gold Coast.

item.title: Major fire at migrant camp on Greek island of Samos
item.description: A major fire that broke out Sunday evening at the Vathy migrant camp on the Greek island of Samos, was brought under control, the Greek Ministry of Migration said.

item.title: Philippines’ Manny Pacquiao to run for president in 2022
item.description: Philippine boxing superstar Manny Pacquiao declared he will run for president in 2022, vowing to tackle poverty and corruption as he seeks to win over voters with his rags-to-riches story.

item.title: Man accused of killing co-worker enters plea
item.description: The man accused of killing Celeste Manno in her home while she slept has pleaded not guilty to murder.
